01:40:39.413 --> 01:40:41.847
I can't get him to come back inside.

01:40:41.916 --> 01:40:46.683
<i>He's just laying out there
in the cold and he won't move.</i>

01:40:59.100 --> 01:41:01.728
<i>- Hey.
- Hi.</i>

01:41:01.802 --> 01:41:04.270
Patrick came home.
We got him here.

01:41:04.338 --> 01:41:09.901
Dr. Platt said that if he's comfortable,
leave him for a while and see, but...

01:41:09.977 --> 01:41:12.741
he's just not getting better.

01:41:15.883 --> 01:41:18.113
All right, I'm gonna take him in.

01:41:19.754 --> 01:41:22.882
<i>- Is he sick again?
- Yeah, he is, honey.</i>

01:41:22.957 --> 01:41:25.084
He doesn't feel too good.

01:41:25.159 --> 01:41:28.151
But I'm gonna take him into the doctor
and they're gonna try to make him feel better.

01:41:28.229 --> 01:41:30.561
It's all right, Marley.
You're gonna be okay.

01:41:36.036 --> 01:41:41.064
You could take Lamby,
but don't chew her other ear off.

01:41:41.142 --> 01:41:43.633
<i>That's sweet, honey.</i>

01:41:43.711 --> 01:41:45.770
Here, I'll take it.

01:41:49.049 --> 01:41:51.074
Good-bye.

01:42:34.862 --> 01:42:36.955
Okay.

01:43:00.054 --> 01:43:03.990
I've tried everything I did last time
that worked, but I'm not having any luck.

01:43:04.058 --> 01:43:07.152
Not able to get the tube down there.

01:43:07.228 --> 01:43:11.062
The stomach is still twisted.
There's still surgery, but-

01:43:11.131 --> 01:43:14.362
He's not strong enough.

01:43:23.344 --> 01:43:26.472
- I like this one the best.
- Which one?

01:43:26.547 --> 01:43:28.879
Oh, the mangoes. Yeah.

01:43:28.949 --> 01:43:32.441
Hello?

01:43:32.520 --> 01:43:34.681
Hey, it's me.

01:43:34.755 --> 01:43:37.451
So, it's his stomach again.

01:43:37.525 --> 01:43:41.791
- And they could do surgery, but-
- I know.

01:43:41.862 --> 01:43:46.731
Do you want me to come down there?

01:43:46.800 --> 01:43:49.701
No, no, I think it's a good idea
to stay with the kids...

01:43:49.770 --> 01:43:52.068
and be with them.

01:43:52.139 --> 01:43:56.633
I'm just gonna-

01:44:03.651 --> 01:44:05.619
I love you, John.

01:44:06.987 --> 01:44:08.978
I love you.

01:44:14.061 --> 01:44:16.894
- All right.
- I'm gonna give you some time.

01:44:16.964 --> 01:44:19.194
- Okay.
- And I'll be right outside if you need me.

01:44:19.266 --> 01:44:21.257
All right. Thanks.

01:44:23.237 --> 01:44:27.401
Look what I got for you.
Remember this?

01:44:27.474 --> 01:44:32.878
What did Colleen say to you?
You remember that?

01:44:32.947 --> 01:44:36.348
You remember chewing up that ear?

01:44:36.417 --> 01:44:40.581
Well, it's tough to remember
all the things you've chewed up, isn't it?

01:44:40.654 --> 01:44:43.350
It all starts to kind of run together.

01:45:17.558 --> 01:45:20.391
It's okay. You don't have to do anything.

01:45:22.229 --> 01:45:25.824
You don't have your usual energy.

01:45:25.899 --> 01:45:29.858
You remember how we were
always saying what a pain you are-

01:45:29.937 --> 01:45:32.428
that you're the world's worst dog?

01:45:34.108 --> 01:45:36.133
Don't believe it.

01:45:36.210 --> 01:45:38.542
Don't believe any
of it for a minute.

01:45:38.612 --> 01:45:42.070
'Cause you know
we couldn't find a better dog.

01:45:44.885 --> 01:45:48.048
You know what made you
such a... great dog-

01:45:48.122 --> 01:45:52.115
is you loved us every day,
no matter what.

01:45:52.192 --> 01:45:54.217
That's an amazing thing.

01:45:54.294 --> 01:45:57.730
You know how much we love you?

01:45:57.798 --> 01:45:59.993
We love you so much.

01:46:03.804 --> 01:46:06.295
I love you more than anything.

01:46:07.708 --> 01:46:12.771
I don't know exactly
where we go from here...

01:46:12.846 --> 01:46:16.577
but I want you to remember
you're a great dog, Marley.

01:46:16.650 --> 01:46:19.642
You're a great dog.

01:46:31.298 --> 01:46:33.892
<i>He won't feel this. He'll just slip away.</i>

01:46:33.967 --> 01:46:35.958
You ready?

01:46:38.605 --> 01:46:40.698
<i>- Yeah, we're ready.
- Okay.</i>

01:48:44.531 --> 01:48:47.557
Okay. Get down.

01:48:53.073 --> 01:48:56.770
<i>- He's wrapped in his blanket.
- So he can stay warm.</i>

01:48:56.844 --> 01:48:59.904
Do you guys wanna read
what you wrote?

01:49:01.782 --> 01:49:03.807
Mine's a picture of me and Marley...

01:49:03.884 --> 01:49:06.512
grasshoppers and ice cream.

01:49:06.587 --> 01:49:08.578
Mommy wrote what I said.

01:49:08.655 --> 01:49:14.059
<i>"Dear Marley, I will
never forget you forever. Colleen. "</i>

01:49:14.127 --> 01:49:16.891
And these are kisses.

01:49:16.964 --> 01:49:19.592
<i>- That's beautiful.
- Thank you.</i>

01:49:19.666 --> 01:49:22.533
You wanna put it in?
He'll like that.

01:49:22.603 --> 01:49:24.867
<i>Set it down.</i>

01:49:26.273 --> 01:49:28.207
Good.

01:49:28.275 --> 01:49:32.143
That's a great picture.
Conor, do you wanna-

01:49:35.582 --> 01:49:38.449
"Dear Marley, I loved you all my life.

01:49:38.518 --> 01:49:41.783
"I hope you like heaven
and that there's lots to chew on.

01:49:41.855 --> 01:49:45.313
<i>Your brother, Conor Richard Grogan. "</i>

01:49:48.862 --> 01:49:51.626
<i>That was a good letter.</i>

01:49:51.698 --> 01:49:54.895
Patrick, do you wanna say something?

01:49:56.203 --> 01:49:59.138
He knows.

01:50:02.242 --> 01:50:04.904
I'd like to give him something.

01:50:11.218 --> 01:50:13.209
This necklace.

01:50:15.055 --> 01:50:17.922
It's been on quite a journey.

01:50:24.131 --> 01:50:27.692
Your dad gave it to me...

01:50:27.768 --> 01:50:31.101
to celebrate the beginning
of our family.

01:50:31.171 --> 01:50:34.038
But, you know-

01:50:34.107 --> 01:50:36.871
Our family had really already begun.

01:50:43.617 --> 01:50:45.710
Bye, Clearance Puppy.

01:51:13.113 --> 01:51:15.274
<i>A dog has no use for fancy cars...</i>

01:51:15.349 --> 01:51:18.546
<i>or big homes or designer clothes.</i>

01:51:18.618 --> 01:51:22.054
<i>A waterlogged stick
will dojust fine.</i>

01:51:22.122 --> 01:51:24.784
<i>A dog doesn't care
if you're rich or poor...</i>

01:51:24.858 --> 01:51:28.259
<i>clever or dull, smart or dumb.</i>

01:51:28.328 --> 01:51:31.661
<i>Give 'em your heart
and he'll give you his.</i>

01:51:37.738 --> 01:51:40.673
<i>How many people
can you say that about?</i>

01:51:40.741 --> 01:51:45.508
<i>How many people can make you
feel rare and pure and special?</i>

01:51:50.350 --> 01:51:55.515
<i>How many people can
make you feel... extraordinary?</i>

